# Flight Follower — Environment Variables
#
# All values are optional — each has a sensible default. The app does NOT
# auto-load .env files; pass these inline (`FOO=bar npm run ...`) or export
# them from your shell profile. Copy this file to .env.local if you want a
# private, gitignored place to keep your own values.

# ─── Server paths ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# JSON file where user settings (e.g. Simbrief pilot ID) are persisted.
# Default: ./server/.data/settings.json
# FF_CONFIG_PATH=./server/.data/settings.json

# Directory served to the browser in production (built React bundle).
# In dev you run Vite separately; this only matters when you run the server
# directly against a production build.
# Default: ./web/dist
# FF_STATIC_PATH=./web/dist

# HTTP + WebSocket port. Both live on the same port.
# Default: 4444
# FF_PORT=4444

# ─── Telemetry recording (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────

# When set, the server appends each MSFS RawTelemetry event to this JSONL
# file as you fly. Opens in append mode — existing recordings are preserved.
# Leave unset for no recording. The CLI `npm run dev:record -- <path>` sets
# this for you.
# Default: unset
# FF_RECORD_PATH=./recordings/flight.jsonl

# ─── Replay harness (scripts/dev-telemetry-replay.ts) ──────────────────────

# Interval in milliseconds between emitted fixture events. 500 ms ≈ 2 Hz,
# matching the WebSocket broadcast rate.
# Default: 500
# REPLAY_TICK_MS=500
